                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The life expectancy of the game is going down.  SoE realizes that people who are signing up now don't/won't have the passion to spend 2+ years getting to the end game like the original players, they want to see the end game now and ingore the unnecessary BS.  In order to draw in more customers you get rid of some of the hurdles originally in place.  Yes, this does take away from the game a little bit, but hell EQ has changed so much that it really doesn't matter anymore.<br /><br />I remember running around with empty or cloth slots on my original toon and still surviving and enjoying the game (rogue and war). Nowdays someone can start a toon with lvl 50 gear for nearly no plat whatsoever.<br /><br />Its basic economics, bigger better faster..and most importantly NOW!  Its just another ploy to get some $ and some new accounts before EQ really starts tapering off.  There are quite a few guilds reaching the end game now, with tons right on their heels.  LDoN will hold interest for a little while, but not that long.  An expansion may keep interest for a few more months, but after that the major guilds are going to go to new games like WoW so they can be the first to reach the top there as well.<br /><br />The skill required to play EQ is virtually non-existant now.  Anyone can get to lvl 65 with little or no knowledge of their class.  Monks, Sk's and necs no longer need to FD pull, there's pac pulling for that.  Mana management is out the widnow with FT items, horses, C5/Canni5/SoS.  Agro management is out the window because everyone knows wars are screwed, they'd rather just get a knight who they know can hold agro so they don't have to worry about it (xp groups here, not raids).  Clerics are in such high demand that all they need to be able to do is learn how to cast in a chain and most guilds will help them learn the rest...I could go on and on...I remember being able to form a pick-up group with just about anyone lfg and know that I'll be able to have fun, now I don't join a group unless there's at least one guildie in it and they tell me they know the group knows what they're doin...<br /><br />well, nough of my ramblings...<br /><br />Nyt</span id="msg"></font></td>
