                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> About the only thing that has been "dumbed down" since I started playing EQ at release is the quality of posts on EQ-related message boards....<br /><br />The EQ Live team isn't dumbing down the game.  They are implementing changes that the original development team didn't have the funds/time to do.  They are correcting blatant mathematical bugs in XP code (e.g. "hell levels"....they were NOT a feature, they were a BUG, and followed logically from the XP modifier that kicked in at level 30, etc.)<br /><br />Here's another hint:  If you hit Backspace you don't NEED sense heading, so why not max it out for newbies so that their compass works properly?<br /><br />EQ is STILL a challenging game to play.  You might think otherwise, but I'll tell you right now that if SoE were to parse character files, they'd most likely find that it's only a very small percent of *individual players* (read: persons behind the keyboard) who have characters that reach 65.  Hell, I've been playing as a casual player, on and off, since release.  My Necro (my primary character) FINALLY hit level 51 a few days ago.  His birthdate is January 15, 1999 (I played a wizard at release and managed to get him up to level 20...yes it was difficult, hehe).  I may never see 65 myself.  But I may never NEED to.  There's plenty of content for me to consume between 51 and 65.<br /><br />EQ isn't being "dumbed down".  What's happening is that many of the *unnecessarily time-consuming* actions are being removed or completely revamped.  Key words here:  unnecessarily time-consuming.  I don't have a problem with "time consuming".  But as a part-time player, I have an ENORMOUS problem with "unnecessarily time consuming".<br /><br />Sense heading, since the release of LoY, has moved from the "time consuming" category to the "unnecessarily time consuming" category.  Why?  Because if you have LoY, all you need to do is open up the automap and you'll know EXACTLY which direction you're facing.  So if that's the case, then remove the need to click the sense heading button umpteen-million times to max it out.<br /><br />I could go on and on, but you get the idea of what I'm trying to say.  I'm firmly planted in the camp that sees many of these changes as positive changes that do much more to enhance the game than destroy it.  I am living proof.  I've quit EQ more times than I care to remember.  But with almost every new expansion comes new modifications (either to the interface or general gameplay) that keep drawing me back in.<br /><br />EverQuest is the "King of MMOGs" for good reason.  It will take something quite extraordinary to dethrone it.  I've beta-tested or played every MMOG out there right now.  And NOTHING keeps me coming back and holds my interest like EQ.  That's why I'm back.  And that's why I'll probably stay a little longer this time.<br /><br />....that's if anyone's interested in my opinion :)</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><hr noshade size="1"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Mujahid Mukhtaar, 61 Necro, Solusek Ro</span></font></td>
                    </tr>
