                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I do feel that a lot of the newbie changes lead to the overall 'dumbing down' of EQ. If everything is given to you at the start, you won't necessarily know how they're obtained, what things do, or even appreciate them. You memorize spells by putting the scroll in your spellbook. Since that's already been done, a new player might not necessarily understand that. I don't know what the help files say because I turned all that shit off. It just seems like you're being held by the hand till you're in the teens. That leads to a path heading straight for Paludal, and the common denominator falls through the floor.<br /><br />But I can also understand that most new chars are probably alts for players who don't want to go through all the lowbie shit again, and that real new players need a head start to get in pace with the 3+ year players. It's a fine line to dance on.<br /><br />Personally I think EQ jumped the shark when they took spellbook medding out....the day after my cleric hit 35 [:-argh]</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
